main event: An object was observed coming down by parachute and was recovered and turned over to the Air Force for identification.
interesting points: The object belonged to the U.S. and was not of foreign technology concern.
The object weighed about 15 lbs, was pale purplish-yellow in color, and appeared to be made of hard plastic with a lead thing in the bottom.
The object had electrical cables of various colors and a red-black box with a male plug.
The object had gears in the bottom that were jammed with sticks to stop the ticking of a clock.
The object had a 15-ft parachute with alternating gold and white rings and a center cone on the bottom, with various markings indicating a U.S. origin.
result: The object was identified as belonging to the U.S. and not of foreign technology concern.
sighted object: An object coming down by parachute
photographs: No photographs were included in the report.
